      <tr>
        <td><span class="status-code s2xx">201</span></td>
        <td>Created</td>
        <td>Resource successfully created; include <code>Location</code> header pointing to new resource</td>
        <td><span class="tag tag-blue">POST</span></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="status-code s2xx">204</span></td>
        <td>No Content</td>
        <td>Success with no body to return (common for DELETE and some PATCHes)</td>
        <td><span class="tag tag-red">DELETE</span><span class="tag" style="background:rgba(167,139,250,.15);color:var(--patch)">PATCH</span></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="status-code s4xx">400</span></td>
        <td>Bad Request</td>
        <td>Malformed JSON, missing required fields, validation failure</td>
        <td><span class="tag tag-blue">POST</span><span class="tag tag-yellow">PUT</span><span class="tag" style="background:rgba(167,139,250,.15);color:var(--patch)">PATCH</span></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="status-code s4xx">401</span></td>
        <td>Unauthorized</td>
        <td>Missing or invalid authentication credentials</td>
        <td>All methods</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="status-code s4xx">403</span></td>
        <td>Forbidden</td>
        <td>Authenticated but lacking permission for this resource</td>
        <td>All methods</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="status-code s4xx">404</span></td>
        <td>Not Found</td>
        <td>Resource with given ID does not exist</td>
        <td><span class="tag tag-green">GET</span><span class="tag tag-yellow">PUT</span><span class="tag" style="background:rgba(167,139,250,.15);color:var(--patch)">PATCH</span><span class="tag tag-red">DELETE</span></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="status-code s4xx">409</span></td>
        <td>Conflict</td>
        <td>Duplicate resource (e.g. email already registered)</td>
        <td><span class="tag tag-blue">POST</span><span class="tag tag-yellow">PUT</span></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><span class="status-code s5xx">500</span></td>
        <td>Internal Server Error</td>
        <td>Unexpected server-side failure; never expose stack traces</td>
        <td>All methods</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <!-- ── REST PRINCIPLES ── -->
  <div class="section-title">📐 Core REST Design Principles</div>

  <div class="principles-grid">
    <div class="principle-card">
      <div class="principle-icon">🎯</div>
      <div class="principle-title">Resources, Not Actions</div>
      <div class="principle-text">URLs name things (nouns), never actions (verbs). The HTTP method conveys the action: GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-card">
      <div class="principle-icon">📦</div>
      <div class="principle-title">Plural Nouns for Collections</div>
      <div class="principle-text">Use <code>/users</code> not <code>/user</code>. Collections are plural; individual items are addressed with an ID: <code>/users/42</code>.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-card">
      <div class="principle-icon">🔒</div>
      <div class="principle-title">Safe &amp; Idempotent Methods</div>
      <div class="principle-text">GET and HEAD must be safe (no side effects). GET, PUT, DELETE, HEAD, OPTIONS must be idempotent. POST is neither.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-card">
      <div class="principle-icon">📝</div>
      <div class="principle-title">Body Over Query String</div>
      <div class="principle-text">Send state-changing data in the request body (JSON), not query parameters. Query strings are for filtering, sorting, and pagination only.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-card">
      <div class="principle-icon">🔤</div>
      <div class="principle-title">Consistent Naming</div>
      <div class="principle-text">Use lowercase kebab-case for paths: <code>/user-profiles</code>. Avoid camelCase, underscores, or mixed conventions across endpoints.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-card">
      <div class="principle-icon">🔢</div>
      <div class="principle-title">Meaningful Status Codes</div>
      <div class="principle-text">Never return 200 OK for an error. Use the correct 2xx, 4xx, or 5xx code so clients can handle responses without parsing the body.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-card">
      <div class="principle-icon">🗂️</div>
      <div class="principle-title">Versioning</div>
      <div class="principle-text">Prefix your API with a version: <code>/api/v1/users</code>. This allows breaking changes without disrupting existing clients.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-card">
      <div class="principle-icon">↩️</div>
      <div class="principle-title">HATEOAS &amp; Location Headers</div>
      <div class="principle-text">After POST (201 Created), return a <code>Location: /users/42</code> header. Optionally embed links in responses to guide clients to related actions.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

</main>

