## What's covered in the page

| Tab | Contents |
|---|---|
| **⚠️ Problems Found** | 4 expandable cards — one per original endpoint — each listing every specific issue tagged by category (Method, Naming, Resource, Security, Design) with a before/after comparison |
| **✅ Corrected Endpoints** | Full spec for each fixed endpoint: query/path params, example JSON request & response, and all relevant HTTP status codes |
| **📖 Best Practices** | 6 reference cards covering nouns vs verbs, plural names, HTTP method semantics, status codes, data security, and versioning/pagination |

### Key issues flagged across all 4 endpoints
1. **`GET /getUsers`** → verb in URL, missing plural, no pagination
2. **`POST /user/delete/5`** → wrong method, verb in URL, singular resource, broken idempotency
3. **`GET /createUser?name=Jo`** → GET for mutation, sensitive data in query string, verb in URL, no validation
4. **`PUT /updateAllUsers`** → PUT semantics misapplied to a collection, verb in URL, dangerous bulk op with no ID

