    <div class="section-title">Core REST Design Principles</div>
    <p style="color:var(--text-muted);font-size:.875rem;margin-bottom:1.25rem;">
      The rules that guided every correction above.
    </p>

    <div class="principle-grid">
      <div class="principle-card">
        <div class="principle-icon">🗂️</div>
        <h3>Use Nouns, Not Verbs</h3>
        <p>URLs identify <em>resources</em>. HTTP methods express the action.
        <code>/users</code> not <code>/getUsers</code> or <code>/deleteUser</code>.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="principle-card">
        <div class="principle-icon">🔢</div>
        <h3>Plural Resource Names</h3>
        <p>Collections use plural nouns (<code>/users</code>), making the distinction between
        a collection and a single item (<code>/users/5</code>) explicit and consistent.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="principle-card">
        <div class="principle-icon">📡</div>
        <h3>Correct HTTP Methods</h3>
        <p><strong>GET</strong> read · <strong>POST</strong> create · <strong>PUT</strong> replace ·
        <strong>PATCH</strong> partial update · <strong>DELETE</strong> remove.
        Never use GET to mutate state.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="principle-card">
        <div class="principle-icon">🔁</div>
        <h3>Idempotency</h3>
        <p>GET, PUT, PATCH, DELETE are idempotent — repeating the same request yields the same
        server state. POST is not; each call may create a new resource.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="principle-card">
        <div class="principle-icon">📦</div>
        <h3>Body Over Query String</h3>
        <p>Send creation/mutation payloads in the request body as JSON, not in query parameters.
        Query strings are for filtering, sorting, and pagination on safe reads.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="principle-card">
        <div class="principle-icon">🔢</div>
        <h3>Meaningful Status Codes</h3>
        <p><code>201</code> for creation, <code>204</code> for no-content responses,
        <code>404</code> for missing resources, <code>422</code> for validation errors.
        Never return <code>200</code> for everything.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="principle-card">
        <div class="principle-icon">🔡</div>
        <h3>Consistent Naming</h3>
        <p>Stick to lowercase, hyphen-separated path segments throughout your API.
        Avoid camelCase, PascalCase, or mixed conventions in URLs.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="principle-card">
        <div class="principle-icon">🔒</div>
        <h3>Security Awareness</h3>
        <p>Never put sensitive data (passwords, tokens) in query strings — they appear in
        server logs, browser history, and referrer headers. Always use the request body.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="principle-card">
        <div class="principle-icon">🏗️</div>
        <h3>Hierarchical Resources</h3>
        <p>Nest related resources logically: <code>/users/5/posts</code> retrieves posts
        belonging to user 5. Keep nesting shallow (max 2–3 levels) to avoid brittle URLs.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div><!-- /tab-principles -->

