<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>REST API Design Review</title>
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #0f1117;
      --surface: #1a1d27;
      --surface2: #22263a;
      --border: #2e3250;
      --accent: #6c63ff;
      --accent2: #48cfad;
      --danger: #ff5c5c;
      --warning: #ffb347;
      --success: #48cfad;
      --text: #e8eaf6;
      --text-muted: #8b90b0;
      --get: #48cfad;
      --post: #6c63ff;
      --put: #ffb347;
      --patch: #4fc3f7;
      --delete: #ff5c5c;
      --radius: 10px;
    }

    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }

    body {
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', system-ui, sans-serif;
      line-height: 1.6;
      min-height: 100vh;
    }

    /* ── Header ── */
    header {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a1d27 0%, #12152a 100%);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      padding: 2.5rem 2rem 2rem;
      text-align: center;
      position: relative;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    header::before {
      content: '';
      position: absolute;
      top: -60px; left: 50%;
      transform: translateX(-50%);
      width: 500px; height: 200px;
      background: radial-gradient(ellipse, rgba(108,99,255,.25) 0%, transparent 70%);
      pointer-events: none;
    }
    header h1 {
      font-size: 2rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: -0.5px;
      background: linear-gradient(90deg, #6c63ff, #48cfad);
      -webkit-background-clip: text;
      -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
      background-clip: text;
    }
    header p {
      color: var(--text-muted);
      margin-top: .5rem;
      font-size: .95rem;
    }
    .badge-row {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: center;
      gap: .75rem;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-top: 1.25rem;
    }
    .badge {
      padding: .25rem .75rem;
      border-radius: 999px;
      font-size: .75rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      letter-spacing: .5px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }
    .badge-purple { background: rgba(108,99,255,.2); color: #a89cff; border: 1px solid rgba(108,99,255,.4); }
    .badge-green  { background: rgba(72,207,173,.15); color: #48cfad; border: 1px solid rgba(72,207,173,.35); }
    .badge-red    { background: rgba(255,92,92,.15);  color: #ff8080; border: 1px solid rgba(255,92,92,.35); }

    /* ── Layout ── */
    main {
      max-width: 1000px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 2rem 1.5rem 4rem;
    }

    /* ── Section titles ── */
    .section-title {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 1px;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      margin: 2.5rem 0 1rem;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: .6rem;
    }
    .section-title::after {
      content: '';
      flex: 1;
      height: 1px;
      background: var(--border);
    }

    /* ── Summary cards ── */
    .summary-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
    }
    .summary-card {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      padding: 1.25rem 1rem;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .summary-card .num {
      font-size: 2.2rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      line-height: 1;
    }
    .summary-card .label {
      font-size: .8rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      margin-top: .35rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: .5px;
    }
    .num-red    { color: var(--danger); }
    .num-green  { color: var(--success); }
    .num-purple { color: var(--accent); }
    .num-yellow { color: var(--warning); }

    /* ── Endpoint card ── */
    .endpoint-card {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
      overflow: hidden;
      transition: border-color .2s;
    }
    .endpoint-card:hover { border-color: var(--accent); }

    .card-header {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 1rem;
      padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
      cursor: pointer;
      user-select: none;
      transition: background .15s;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }
    .card-header:hover { background: rgba(255,255,255,.03); }

    .method-badge {
      padding: .3rem .7rem;
      border-radius: 6px;
      font-size: .75rem;
      font-weight: 800;
      letter-spacing: .8px;
      min-width: 62px;
      text-align: center;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }
    .m-get    { background: rgba(72,207,173,.15);  color: var(--get);    border: 1px solid rgba(72,207,173,.4); }
    .m-post   { background: rgba(108,99,255,.15);  color: var(--post);   border: 1px solid rgba(108,99,255,.4); }
    .m-put    { background: rgba(255,179,71,.15);  color: var(--put);    border: 1px solid rgba(255,179,71,.4); }
    .m-patch  { background: rgba(79,195,247,.15);  color: var(--patch);  border: 1px solid rgba(79,195,247,.4); }
    .m-delete { background: rgba(255,92,92,.15);   color: var(--delete); border: 1px solid rgba(255,92,92,.4); }

    .endpoint-path {
      font-family: 'Cascadia Code', 'Fira Code', 'Consolas', monospace;
      font-size: .95rem;
      color: var(--text);
      flex: 1;
    }
    .endpoint-summary {
      font-size: .82rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
    }
    .chevron {
      margin-left: auto;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      font-size: .8rem;
      transition: transform .25s;
      flex-shrink: 0;
    }
    .card-header.open .chevron { transform: rotate(180deg); }

    /* ── Card body ── */
    .card-body {
      display: none;
      padding: 0 1.25rem 1.25rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .card-body.open { display: block; }

    /* ── Problems / fixes tabs ── */
    .tabs {
      display: flex;
      gap: .5rem;
      margin: 1rem 0 .75rem;
    }
    .tab-btn {
      padding: .35rem .9rem;
      border-radius: 6px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      background: transparent;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      font-size: .82rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      cursor: pointer;
      transition: all .15s;
    }
    .tab-btn:hover { border-color: var(--accent); color: var(--text); }
    .tab-btn.active {
      background: var(--accent);
      border-color: var(--accent);
      color: #fff;
    }
    .tab-btn.active-green {
      background: var(--success);
      border-color: var(--success);
      color: #0f1117;
    }
    .tab-panel { display: none; }
    .tab-panel.active { display: block; }

    /* ── Problem list ── */
    .problem-list { list-style: none; }
    .problem-list li {
      display: flex;
      gap: .75rem;
      padding: .6rem 0;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      font-size: .88rem;
    }
    .problem-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .problem-icon { font-size: 1rem; flex-shrink: 0; margin-top: .1rem; }
    .problem-text strong {
      display: block;
      color: #ff8080;
      margin-bottom: .15rem;
    }
    .problem-text span { color: var(--text-muted); }

    /* ── Comparison box ── */
    .comparison {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: .5rem;
    }
    @media(max-width:600px){ .comparison { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }

    .comp-box {
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 1rem;
      font-size: .85rem;
    }
    .comp-bad  { background: rgba(255,92,92,.08);  border: 1px solid rgba(255,92,92,.3); }
    .comp-good { background: rgba(72,207,173,.08); border: 1px solid rgba(72,207,173,.3); }
    .comp-box h4 {
      font-size: .72rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: .8px;
      margin-bottom: .6rem;
    }
    .comp-bad  h4 { color: var(--danger); }
    .comp-good h4 { color: var(--success); }
    .comp-box code {
      display: block;
      font-family: 'Cascadia Code','Fira Code','Consolas',monospace;
      background: rgba(0,0,0,.3);
      padding: .4rem .6rem;
      border-radius: 5px;
      margin-bottom: .4rem;
      word-break: break-all;
    }
    .comp-bad  code { color: #ff8080; }
    .comp-good code { color: #48cfad; }

    /* ── Status codes table ── */
    .status-table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      font-size: .84rem;
      margin-top: .5rem;
    }
    .status-table th {
      text-align: left;
      padding: .5rem .75rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      font-size: .75rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: .5px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    .status-table td {
      padding: .55rem .75rem;
      border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(46,50,80,.5);
      vertical-align: top;
    }
    .status-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
    .sc {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: .15rem .5rem;
      border-radius: 5px;
      font-family: monospace;
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: .82rem;
    }
    .sc-2 { background: rgba(72,207,173,.15);  color: #48cfad; }
    .sc-4 { background: rgba(255,179,71,.15);  color: #ffb347; }
    .sc-5 { background: rgba(255,92,92,.15);   color: #ff5c5c; }

    /* ── Request/Response example ── */
    .example-block {
      background: #12152a;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: 8px;
      margin-top: .75rem;
      overflow: hidden;
    }
    .example-block-title {
      padding: .4rem .85rem;
      font-size: .72rem;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: .8px;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      background: rgba(255,255,255,.03);
    }
    .example-block pre {
      padding: .85rem 1rem;
      font-family: 'Cascadia Code','Fira Code','Consolas',monospace;
      font-size: .82rem;
      color: #c8d3f5;
      overflow-x: auto;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }
    .json-key   { color: #7ec8e3; }
    .json-str   { color: #a8e6cf; }
    .json-num   { color: #ffb347; }
    .json-bool  { color: #ff8080; }
    .http-method { color: #6c63ff; font-weight: 700; }
    .http-path   { color: #48cfad; }
    .http-header { color: #7ec8e3; }
    .http-value  { color: #a8e6cf; }

    /* ── Principles section ── */
    .principles-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
      gap: 1rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }
    .principle-card {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      padding: 1.1rem 1rem;
      transition: border-color .2s, transform .2s;
    }
    .principle-card:hover { border-color: var(--accent); transform: translateY(-2px); }
    .principle-icon { font-size: 1.6rem; margin-bottom: .5rem; }
    .principle-card h3 { font-size: .9rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: .3rem; }
    .principle-card p  { font-size: .8rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.5; }

    /* ── Quick reference ── */
    .methods-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(170px, 1fr));
      gap: .75rem;
      margin-top: 1rem;
    }
    .method-card {
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
      border-radius: var(--radius);
      padding: .9rem 1rem;
    }
    .method-card .m-label {
      font-weight: 800;
      font-size: .9rem;
      font-family: monospace;
      margin-bottom: .35rem;
    }
    .method-card p { font-size: .78rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.4; }
    .method-card .idempotent {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-top: .4rem;
      font-size: .68rem;
      padding: .1rem .45rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .yes { background: rgba(72,207,173,.15); color: #48cfad; }
    .no  { background: rgba(255,92,92,.15);  color: #ff8080; }

    /* ── Scrollbar ── */
    ::-webkit-scrollbar { width: 6px; height: 6px; }
    ::-webkit-scrollbar-track { background: var(--bg); }
    ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb { background: var(--border); border-radius: 3px; }

    /* ── Tooltip ── */
    [data-tip] { position: relative; cursor: help; }
    [data-tip]::after {
      content: attr(data-tip);
      position: absolute;
      bottom: calc(100% + 6px);
      left: 50%;
      transform: translateX(-50%);
      background: #2e3250;
      color: var(--text);
      padding: .35rem .65rem;
      border-radius: 6px;
      font-size: .75rem;
      white-space: nowrap;
      pointer-events: none;
      opacity: 0;
      transition: opacity .15s;
      z-index: 10;
      border: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
    [data-tip]:hover::after { opacity: 1; }

    /* ── Footer ── */
    footer {
      text-align: center;
      padding: 2rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      font-size: .8rem;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <h1>🔍 REST API Design Review</h1>
  <p>User Management System — Endpoint Audit &amp; Correction Guide</p>
  <div class="badge-row">
    <span class="badge badge-red">4 Problematic Endpoints</span>
    <span class="badge badge-purple">14 Design Issues Found</span>
    <span class="badge badge-green">4 Corrected Endpoints</span>
  </div>
</header>

<main>

  <!-- Summary -->
  <div class="section-title">📊 Audit Summary</div>
  <div class="summary-grid">
    <div class="summary-card">
      <div class="num num-red">4</div>
      <div class="label">Bad Endpoints</div>
    </div>
    <div class="summary-card">
      <div class="num num-yellow">14</div>
      <div class="label">Issues Found</div>
    </div>
    <div class="summary-card">
      <div class="num num-green">4</div>
      <div class="label">Fixed Endpoints</div>
    </div>
    <div class="summary-card">
      <div class="num num-purple">5</div>
      <div class="label">HTTP Methods Used</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════
       ENDPOINT 1 — GET /getUsers
  ══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="section-title">🚨 Problematic Endpoints</div>

  <!-- Card 1 -->
  <div class="endpoint-card" id="card1">
    <div class="card-header" onclick="toggleCard('card1')">
      <span class="method-badge m-get">GET</span>
      <span class="endpoint-path">/getUsers</span>
      <span class="endpoint-summary">Retrieve all users</span>
      <span class="chevron">▼</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <div class="tabs">
        <button class="tab-btn active"    onclick="switchTab(this,'c1-problems')">⚠️ Problems</button>
        <button class="tab-btn"           onclick="switchTab(this,'c1-fix')">✅ Fixed Version</button>
        <button class="tab-btn"           onclick="switchTab(this,'c1-status')">📋 Status Codes</button>
        <button class="tab-btn"           onclick="switchTab(this,'c1-example')">💡 Example</button>
      </div>

      <!-- Problems -->
      <div class="tab-panel active" id="c1-problems">
        <ul class="problem-list">
          <li>
            <span class="problem-icon">🔴</span>
            <div class="problem-text">
              <strong>Verb in URL path</strong>
              <span>"getUsers" uses an action word. REST URLs should represent <em>resources</em> (nouns), not actions. The HTTP method already communicates the action.</span>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="problem-icon">🔴</span>
            <div class="problem-text">
              <strong>Camel case naming</strong>
              <span>"getUsers" mixes casing styles. REST convention mandates lowercase, hyphen-separated paths (kebab-case) for readability and consistency.</span>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="problem-icon">🟡</span>
            <div class="problem-text">
              <strong>No versioning</strong>
              <span>There is no API version prefix (e.g., <code>/v1/</code>). Without versioning, future breaking changes cannot be introduced safely.</span>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="problem-icon">🟡</span>
            <div class="problem-text">
              <strong>No pagination support</strong>
              <span>Fetching all users without query params like <code>?page=1&limit=20</code> will cause performance issues at scale and is not REST-idiomatic.</span>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Fix -->
      <div class="tab-panel" id="c1-fix">
        <div class="comparison">
          <div class="comp-box comp-bad">
            <h4>❌ Original</h4>
            <code>GET /getUsers</code>
            <p style="color:var(--text-muted);font-size:.8rem">Verb in path, camelCase, no version, no pagination.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="comp-box comp-good">
            <h4>✅ Corrected</h4>
            <code>GET /v1/users</code>
            <code>GET /v1/users?page=1&amp;limit=20</code>
            <p style="color:var(--text-muted);font-size:.8rem">Noun resource, lowercase, versioned, pagination-ready.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Status Codes -->
      <div class="tab-panel" id="c1-status">
        <table class="status-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Code</th><th>Meaning</th><th>When to use</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><span class="sc sc-2">200 OK</span></td><td>Success</td><td>Users list returned successfully</td></tr>
            <tr><td><span class="sc sc-4">400 Bad Request</span></td><td>Invalid query params</td><td>e.g., <code>?page=-1</code> or non-numeric limit</td></tr>
            <tr><td><span class="sc sc-4">401 Unauthorized</span></td><td>Not authenticated</td><td>Missing or invalid auth token</td></tr>
            <tr><td><span class="sc sc-4">403 Forbidden</span></td><td>Not authorized</td><td>Authenticated but lacks permission</td></tr>
            <tr><td><span class="sc sc-5">500 Internal Server Error</span></td><td>Server failure</td><td>Unexpected database or server error</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Example -->
      <div class="tab-panel" id="c1-example">
        <div class="example-block">
          <div class="example-block-title">Request</div>
          <pre><span class="http-method">GET</span> <span class="http-path">/v1/users?page=1&limit=20</span> HTTP/1.1
<span class="http-header">Host:</span> <span class="http-value">api.example.com</span>
<span class="http-header">Authorization:</span> <span class="http-value">Bearer eyJhbGci...</span>
<span class="http-header">Accept:</span> <span class="http-value">application/json</span></pre>
        </div>
        <div class="example-block">
          <div class="example-block-title">Response — 200 OK</div>
          <pre>{
  <span class="json-key">"data"</span>: [
    { <span class="json-key">"id"</span>: <span class="json-num">1</span>, <span class="json-key">"name"</span>: <span class="json-str">"Alice"</span>, <span class="json-key">"email"</span>: <span class="json-str">"alice@example.com"</span> },
    { <span class="json-key">"id"</span>: <span class="json-num">2</span>, <span class="json-key">"name"</span>: <span class="json-str">"Bob"</span>,   <span class="json-key">"email"</span>: <span class="json-str">"bob@example.com"</span>   }
  ],
  <span class="json-key">"pagination"</span>: {
    <span class="json-key">"page"</span>:       <span class="json-num">1</span>,
    <span class="json-key">"limit"</span>:      <span class="json-num">20</span>,
    <span class="json-key">"total"</span>:      <span class="json-num">142</span>,
    <span class="json-key">"totalPages"</span>: <span class="json-num">8</span>
  }
}</pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════
       ENDPOINT 2 — POST /user/delete/5
  ══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="endpoint-card" id="card2">
    <div class="card-header" onclick="toggleCard('card2')">
      <span class="method-badge m-post">POST</span>
      <span class="endpoint-path">/user/delete/5</span>
      <span class="endpoint-summary">Delete a user by ID</span>
      <span class="chevron">▼</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <div class="tabs">
        <button class="tab-btn active" onclick="switchTab(this,'c2-problems')">⚠️ Problems</button>
        <button class="tab-btn"        onclick="switchTab(this,'c2-fix')">✅ Fixed Version</button>
        <button class="tab-btn"        onclick="switchTab(this,'c2-status')">📋 Status Codes</button>
        <button class="tab-btn"        onclick="switchTab(this,'c2-example')">💡 Example</button>
      </div>

      <div class="tab-panel active" id="c2-problems">
        <ul class="problem-list">
          <li>
            <span class="problem-icon">🔴</span>
            <div class="problem-text">
              <strong>Wrong HTTP method (POST instead of DELETE)</strong>
              <span>POST is for creating resources. Deleting a resource must use the <code>DELETE</code> method, which is semantically correct and allows caches/proxies to behave properly.</span>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="problem-icon">🔴</span>
            <div class="problem-text">
              <strong>Verb "delete" in the URL path</strong>
              <span>The action "delete" is already expressed by the HTTP method. Embedding it in the URL is redundant and violates REST's resource-oriented architecture.</span>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="problem-icon">🔴</span>
            <div class="problem-text">
              <strong>Singular resource name "user"</strong>
              <span>REST convention uses plural nouns for collections (<code>/users</code>). Singular forms create inconsistency across the API surface.</span>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="problem-icon">🟡</span>
            <div class="problem-text">
              <strong>No versioning prefix</strong>
              <span>Same issue as endpoint 1 — missing <code>/v1/</code> makes future evolution risky.</span>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="tab-panel" id="c2-fix">
        <div class="comparison">
          <div class="comp-box comp-bad">
            <h4>❌ Original</h4>
            <code>POST /user/delete/5</code>
            <p style="color:var(--text-muted);font-size:.8rem">Wrong method, verb in path, singular noun, no version.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="comp-box comp-good">
            <h4>✅ Corrected</h4>
            <code>DELETE /v1/users/5</code>
            <p style="color:var(--text-muted);font-size:.8rem">Correct DELETE method, noun-only path, plural, versioned.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="tab-panel" id="c2-status">
        <table class="status-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Code</th><th>Meaning</th><th>When to use</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td><span class="sc sc-2">204 No Content</span></td><td>Deleted successfully</td><td>Resource deleted; no body needed in response</td></tr>
            <tr><td><span class="sc sc-2">200 OK</span></td><td>Deleted with body</td><td>If you return the deleted resource in the response</td></tr>
            <tr><td><span class="sc sc-4">401 Unauthorized</span></td><td>Not authenticated</td><td>Missing or invalid auth token</td></tr>
            <tr><td><span class="sc sc-4">403 Forbidden</span></td><td>Not authorized</td><td>Cannot delete another user's account without admin</td></tr>
            <tr><td><span class="sc sc-4">404 Not Found</span></td><td>User doesn't exist</td><td>ID 5 does not exist in the database</td></tr>
            <tr><td><span class="sc sc-5">500 Internal Server Error</span></td><td>Server failure</td><td>Unexpected error during deletion</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <div class="tab-panel" id="c2-example">
        <div class="example-block">
          <div class="example-block-title">Request</div>
          <pre><span class="http-method">DELETE</span> <span class="http-path">/v1/users/5</span> HTTP/1.1
<span class="http-header">Host:</span> <span class="http-value">api.example.com</span>
<span class="http-header">Authorization:</span> <span class="http-value">Bearer eyJhbGci...</span></pre>
        </div>
        <div class="example-block">
          <div class="example-block-title">Response — 204 No Content</div>
          <pre><span class="http-header">HTTP/1.1</span> <span class="json-num">204</span> No Content
<span class="http-header">Content-Length:</span> <span class="http-value">0</span>

<span style="color:var(--text-muted)">// No response body — deletion was successful</span></pre>
        </div>
        <div class="example-block">
          <div class="example-block-title">Response — 404 Not Found</div>
          <pre>{
  <span class="json-key">"error"</span>: {
    <span class="json-key">"code"</span>:    <span class="json-num">404</span>,
    <span class="json-key">"message"</span>: <span class="json-str">"User with ID 5 not found"</span>,
    <span class="json-key">"path"</span>:    <span class="json-str">"/v1/users/5"</span>
  }
}</pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- ══════════════════════════════════════════
       ENDPOINT 3 — GET /createUser?name=Jo
  ══════════════════════════════════════════ -->
  <div class="endpoint-card" id="card3">
    <div class="card-header" onclick="toggleCard('card3')">
      <span class="method-badge m-get">GET</span>
      <span class="endpoint-path">/createUser?name=Jo</span>
      <span class="endpoint-summary">Create a new user</span>
      <span class="chevron">▼</span>
    </div>
    <div class="card-body">
      <div class="tabs">
        <button class="tab-btn active" onclick="switchTab(this,'c3-problems')">⚠️ Problems</button>
        <button class="tab-btn"        onclick="switchTab(this,'c3-fix')">✅ Fixed Version</button>
        <button class="tab-btn"        onclick="switchTab(this,'c3-status')">📋 Status Codes</button>
        <button class="tab-btn"        onclick="switchTab(this,'c3-example')">💡 Example</button>
      </div>

      <div class="tab-panel active" id="c3-problems">
        <ul class="problem-list">
          <li>
            <span class="problem-icon">🔴</span>
            <div class="problem-text">
              <strong>Wrong HTTP method (GET instead of POST)</strong>
              <span>GET is a safe, idempotent method for <em>reading</em> data. Creating a resource must use POST. Using GET to mutate state violates HTTP semantics — GET requests can be cached, bookmarked, or pre-fetched, causing unintended duplicate user creation.</span>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="problem-icon">🔴</span>
            <div class="problem-text">
              <strong>Sensitive data in query string</strong>
              <span>Query parameters are logged in server access logs, browser history, and proxy caches. User data (name, email, password) must be sent in the <strong>request body</strong>, not the URL.</span>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="problem-icon">🔴</span>
            <div class="problem-text">
              <strong>Verb "createUser" in URL</strong>
              <span>Same anti-pattern — actions belong in HTTP methods, not URL paths. The URL should be the resource (<code>/users</code>), the method (POST) implies creation.</span>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="problem-icon">🔴</span>
            <div class="problem-text">
              <strong>CamelCase URL</strong>
              <span>"createUser" violates kebab-case convention. All paths should be lowercase.</span>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="problem-icon">🟡</span>
            <div class="problem-text">
              <strong>No versioning prefix</strong>
              <span>Missing <code>/v1/</code> API version prefix.</span>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="tab-panel" id="c3-fix">
