</div>

<!-- ===== REST PRINCIPLES ===== -->
<div class="section-title">📐 REST Principles Applied</div>
<div class="principles-grid">
    <div class="principle-card">
        <div class="principle-icon">🎯</div>
        <div class="principle-title">Resource-Based URLs</div>
        <div class="principle-desc">URLs identify resources (nouns), not actions. Use <code style="color:#818cf8">/users</code> not <code style="color:#f87171">/getUsers</code>. The HTTP method describes the action.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-card">
        <div class="principle-icon">⚡</div>
        <div class="principle-title">Correct HTTP Methods</div>
        <div class="principle-desc">GET=read, POST=create, PUT=replace, PATCH=partial update, DELETE=remove. Never use GET or POST as a workaround for DELETE.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-card">
        <div class="principle-icon">🔢</div>
        <div class="principle-title">Meaningful Status Codes</div>
        <div class="principle-desc">200 OK, 201 Created, 204 No Content, 400 Bad Request, 404 Not Found, 409 Conflict, 500 Server Error — each tells a clear story.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-card">
        <div class="principle-icon">📦</div>
        <div class="principle-title">Request Body over Query Params</div>
        <div class="principle-desc">Sensitive or complex data belongs in the request body, not query strings. Query params are for filtering, sorting, and pagination.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-card">
        <div class="principle-icon">🔗</div>
        <div class="principle-title">Consistent Naming</div>
        <div class="principle-desc">Use lowercase, hyphenated, plural nouns. <code style="color:#818cf8">/users</code> not <code style="color:#f87171">/getUsers</code>, <code style="color:#f87171">/updateAllUsers</code>, or <code style="color:#f87171">/User</code>.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-card">
        <div class="principle-icon">🛡️</div>
        <div class="principle-title">Idempotency</div>
        <div class="principle-desc">GET, PUT, DELETE should be idempotent — calling them multiple times yields the same result. POST is not idempotent by design.</div>
    </div>
</div>

